<h1 class="mt-4 mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>

<p>At Pharmastock, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how your personal information is collected, used, and safeguarded when you use our application.</p>

<h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Account Information:</strong> When you register, we collect your email address and nickname.</li>
    <li><strong>Location Data:</strong> Pharmacists may be asked to select or share a pharmacy location for functionality purposes.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> We may collect information about your interaction with the application to improve user experience.</li>
</ul>

<h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
<ul>
    <li>To provide secure login and user role access.</li>
    <li>To allow role-based features, such as inventory management or report generation.</li>
    <li>To improve the performance and security of our application.</li>
</ul>

<h3>3. Sharing Your Data</h3>
<p>We do not sell, trade, or rent users’ personal information to others. Data is only shared internally within your organization as needed for role-based access and functionality.</p>

<h3>4. Data Security</h3>
<p>We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect your personal data against unauthorized access, accidental loss, destruction, or damage.</p>

<h3>5. Your Rights</h3>
<p>You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal data stored in our application. Please contact support for any privacy-related requests.</p>

<h3>6. Changes to This Policy</h3>
<p>This Privacy Policy may be updated occasionally to reflect changes in our practices or legal obligations. Please review it periodically.</p>

<h3>Contact Us</h3>
<p>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact our support team.</p>
